# Non-Refactoring Architecture Rules

Apply these rules to ALL development in this repository:

- Do NOT refactor unrelated modules.
- Do NOT change existing stable architecture unnecessarily.
- Do NOT break authentication, dashboards, APIs, permissions, notifications, or existing modules.
- Extend existing functionality only.
- Preserve backward compatibility.
- Use modular additions and safe migrations only.
- Every major table must continue using `institution_id`.
- All changes must be production-safe and scalable.

When adding features:
- Prefer new migrations, seeders, routes, and controllers over modifying stable code paths.
- Keep existing role slugs and permission names working unless explicitly migrating them.
- Test auth and core dashboards after any permission or auth change.
